cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.MA

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the problem of localizing wireless devices in an ad-hoc network, which is a networking problem. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the problem of inferring the positions of wireless devices from incomplete and inaccurate local distance measurements, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes centralized and distributed positioning algorithms for the localization problem, which can be seen as control systems. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper analyzes the performance of the proposed algorithms and provides a bound on the resulting error, which involves data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper deals with the problem of localizing multiple wireless devices in an ad-hoc network, which can be seen as a multiagent system.
